<body>
<div class="page">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">Year 11 Society & Culture · Week 1, Lesson 4 · Self-directed</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title">"Adolescence is a Western invention" — agree or disagree?</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Today you will look at the evidence, form a position, and write your argument. Your casual teacher is here if you need help — otherwise work through each section at your own pace.</p>
    <div class="hero-tags">
      <span class="hero-tag"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 60 minutes</span>
      <span class="hero-tag"><i class="ti ti-sections"></i> 5 sections</span>
      <span class="hero-tag"><i class="ti ti-forms"></i> Submit at the end</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- RELIEF BANNER -->
  <div class="relief-banner">
    <i class="ti ti-info-circle"></i>
    <div>
      <p class="relief-label">Note for casual teacher</p>
      <p class="relief-text">Thank you for covering this class. Please read the following aloud to students then step back — they work independently through this page.<br><br>
      <strong>"Last lesson you looked at how different cultures experience adolescence. Today you are going to form your own argument about whether adolescence is universal or a Western construct. Work through each section on your laptop. At the end, submit your work using the Google Form link at the bottom. You have the full lesson."</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROGRESS -->
  <div class="progress-row">
    <span class="prog-label">Progress</span>
    <div class="prog-step active" id="p1"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="p2"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="p3"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="p4"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="p5"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 1 — RECALL -->
  <div class="section-card s1">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">1</div>
      <p class="section-title">Recall — what did we find last lesson?</p>
      <span class="section-time"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 8 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="recall-strip">
        <div class="recall-icon"><i class="ti ti-refresh"></i></div>
        <div>
          <p class="recall-label">Last lesson recap</p>
          <p class="recall-text">In Lesson 3 you explored how four different cultures experience the transition from childhood to adulthood — Aboriginal initiation, Japanese Seijin-no-Hi, Amish Rumspringa, and rural communities globally. Today we use that knowledge to build an argument.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="prose">Before we get into new content, look at these numbers:</p>
      <div class="stat-row">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-num" style="color:#7F77DD">1904</p>
          <p class="stat-label">Year G. Stanley Hall first defined "adolescence"</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-num" style="color:#1D9E75">195+</p>
          <p class="stat-label">Countries in the world — most without the same concept</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <p class="stat-num" style="color:#D85A30">~120</p>
          <p class="stat-label">Years the Western idea of adolescence has existed</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="activity-box">
        <p class="activity-label"><i class="ti ti-message"></i> Quick think</p>
        <p class="activity-q">Looking at those numbers — what strikes you? What do they suggest about how "universal" adolescence really is?</p>
        <p class="think-prompt">No need to write this down — just get your brain warmed up.</p>
      </div>
      <button class="complete-btn" id="btn1" onclick="markDone(1)"><i class="ti ti-check"></i> Mark section complete</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 2 — THE DEBATE -->
  <div class="section-card s2">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">2</div>
      <p class="section-title">The structured controversy — two sides</p>
      <span class="section-time"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 12 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">Read both sides of the argument carefully. You will use this evidence in your PEEL paragraph later.</p>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <span class="quote-mark">"</span>
        <p class="quote-text">Adolescence is not a biological fact. It is a social space created by industrialised societies that needed to keep young people in school and out of the workforce.</p>
        <p class="quote-source">— Paraphrased from sociological critiques of Western developmental theory</p>
      </div>

      <p class="prose" style="font-weight:600;color:#D85A30;font-size:13px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em">Side A — Adolescence IS a Western construct</p>
      <div class="evidence-list">
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#D85A30"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">The concept was formally invented in 1904 by G. Stanley Hall — it does not appear in most pre-industrial or non-Western societies in the same form.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#D85A30"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">Compulsory schooling created the conditions for adolescence — when children worked alongside adults, there was no "in between" stage.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#D85A30"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">In many Aboriginal Australian cultures, initiation ceremonies mark a clear transition to adulthood — there is no prolonged identity exploration period.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#D85A30"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">In rural communities across Asia and Africa, young people take on adult economic responsibilities from an early age — the protected teenage years do not exist.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="prose" style="font-weight:600;color:#1D9E75;font-size:13px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;margin-top:1rem">Side B — Adolescence IS universal in some form</p>
      <div class="evidence-list">
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#1D9E75"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">Puberty is a biological universal — every culture must find a way to manage the transition from child to adult body, even if they do it differently.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#1D9E75"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">Amish Rumspringa shows that even non-Western, non-industrialised cultures recognise a transitional period of exploration before full adult commitment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#1D9E75"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">Japanese Seijin-no-Hi suggests all cultures mark the moment of becoming adult — the form differs but the recognition of transition is universal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-item">
          <div class="evidence-dot" style="background:#1D9E75"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="evidence-text">Neuroscience shows the adolescent brain is genuinely distinct — the prefrontal cortex is still developing until the mid-20s regardless of culture.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="complete-btn" id="btn2" onclick="markDone(2)"><i class="ti ti-check"></i> Mark section complete</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 3 — IMAGES -->
  <div class="section-card s3">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">3</div>
      <p class="section-title">See it — growing up around the world</p>
      <span class="section-time"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 8 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">Look at each image below. For each one think about which side of the argument it supports — and why.</p>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <div class="image-card">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1528360983277-13d401cdc186?w=600&q=80" alt="Traditional Japanese ceremony with kimono" loading="lazy">
          <div class="image-card-body">
            <p class="image-card-title">Seijin-no-Hi, Japan</p>
            <p class="image-card-desc">Young adults in formal kimono at the national Coming of Age ceremony — a clear, defined cultural marker.</p>
            <span class="image-card-tag tag-complex">Supports both sides</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-card">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1497486751825-1233686d5d80?w=600&q=80" alt="Students in classroom" loading="lazy">
          <div class="image-card-body">
            <p class="image-card-title">Compulsory schooling, West</p>
            <p class="image-card-desc">School keeps young people economically dependent — the condition that created the Western idea of adolescence.</p>
            <span class="image-card-tag tag-challenge">Challenges universality</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-card">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516026672322-bc52d61a55d5?w=600&q=80" alt="Young person working in a field" loading="lazy">
          <div class="image-card-body">
            <p class="image-card-title">Youth labour, rural communities</p>
            <p class="image-card-desc">In many parts of the world young people work alongside adults from an early age — no protected teenage years.</p>
            <span class="image-card-tag tag-challenge">Challenges universality</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-card">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529156069898-49953e39b3ac?w=600&q=80" alt="Group of teenagers together" loading="lazy">
          <div class="image-card-body">
            <p class="image-card-title">Peer culture, global teens</p>
            <p class="image-card-desc">Social media and global youth culture mean teenagers worldwide increasingly share similar experiences — is adolescence becoming more universal?</p>
            <span class="image-card-tag tag-support">Supports universality</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a class="video-block" href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=is+adolescence+a+social+construct+documentary" target="_blank">
        <div class="video-icon"><i class="ti ti-player-play"></i></div>
        <div style="flex:1">
          <p class="video-title">Is adolescence a social construct?</p>
          <p class="video-meta">Search YouTube · pick a short clip (5 min max) · optional but recommended</p>
        </div>
        <i class="ti ti-external-link" style="color:#9b9b98;font-size:16px"></i>
      </a>
      <button class="complete-btn" id="btn3" onclick="markDone(3)"><i class="ti ti-check"></i> Mark section complete</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 4 — PEEL -->
  <div class="section-card s4">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">4</div>
      <p class="section-title">Form your argument — PEEL paragraph</p>
      <span class="section-time"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 15 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">Now it is time to pick your position and build your argument. First — where do you stand?</p>
      <div class="controversy-grid">
        <div class="controversy-card cv-agree" onclick="selectPosition(this)">
          <p class="cv-title">I agree — it is a Western construct</p>
          <p class="cv-desc">The evidence shows adolescence was invented by industrialised societies and does not apply universally</p>
        </div>
        <div class="controversy-card cv-disagree" onclick="selectPosition(this)">
          <p class="cv-title">I disagree — it is universal</p>
          <p class="cv-desc">All cultures must manage the transition to adulthood — adolescence exists everywhere, just in different forms</p>
        </div>
        <div class="controversy-card cv-partly" onclick="selectPosition(this)">
          <p class="cv-title">I partly agree — the biological transition is universal, but the social experience of adolescence is not</p>
          <p class="cv-desc">Puberty happens everywhere but the "in between" social status, identity exploration, and economic dependence are specific to Western industrialised societies</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="activity-box">
        <p class="activity-label"><i class="ti ti-pencil"></i> PEEL paragraph — type your answer into the Google Form</p>
        <p class="activity-q">Write a PEEL paragraph responding to: <em>"Adolescence is a Western social construct and is not valid for all cultures."</em></p>
        <div class="peel-box">
          <div class="peel-row">
            <div class="peel-letter" style="background:#EEEDFE;color:#3C3489">P</div>
            <div>
              <p class="peel-name">Point</p>
              <p class="peel-hint">State your position clearly — agree, disagree, or partly agree. One sentence.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="peel-row">
            <div class="peel-letter" style="background:#E1F5EE;color:#085041">E</div>
            <div>
              <p class="peel-name">Evidence</p>
              <p class="peel-hint">Use at least ONE piece of evidence from Section 2 or a cultural example from Lesson 3.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="peel-row">
            <div class="peel-letter" style="background:#FAECE7;color:#712B13">E</div>
            <div>
              <p class="peel-name">Explain</p>
              <p class="peel-hint">How does your evidence prove your point? Don't just describe it — connect it to your argument.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="peel-row">
            <div class="peel-letter" style="background:#E6F1FB;color:#0C447C">L</div>
            <div>
              <p class="peel-name">Link</p>
              <p class="peel-hint">Return to the statement — is adolescence a valid concept for all cultures?</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="complete-btn" id="btn4" onclick="markDone(4)"><i class="ti ti-check"></i> Mark section complete</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 5 — REFLECTION + SUBMIT -->
  <div class="section-card s5">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-num">5</div>
      <p class="section-title">Reflection and submit</p>
      <span class="section-time"><i class="ti ti-clock"></i> 10 min</span>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">Almost done. Before you submit, take a moment to reflect on both lessons together.</p>
      <div class="activity-box" style="margin-bottom:1rem">
        <p class="activity-label"><i class="ti ti-pencil"></i> Short reflection — type your answers into the Google Form</p>
        <p class="activity-q">1. Across Lessons 3 and 4, which cultural example most challenged how you think about growing up — and why?</p>
        <p class="activity-q" style="margin-top:10px">2. Do you think the concept of adolescence is becoming more universal because of social media and global culture — or less relevant because of what we now know about cultural difference? Explain your thinking in 3–4 sentences.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="prose">Once your PEEL paragraph and reflection are ready, click below to submit.</p>
      <div class="form-box">
        <div class="form-icon"><i class="ti ti-forms"></i></div>
        <div class="form-text">
          <p class="form-title">Submit your work — Lesson 4</p>
          <p class="form-sub">PEEL paragraph + reflection questions</p>
        </div>
        <a class="form-btn" href="PASTE_YOUR_GOOGLE_FORM_LINK_HERE" target="_blank">Open form ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
<script>
function selectPosition(el){
  document.querySelectorAll('.controversy-card').forEach(c=>c.classList.remove('selected'));
  el.classList.add('selected');
}
function markDone(n){
  var btn=document.getElementById('btn'+n);
  btn.classList.add('done');
  btn.innerHTML='<i class="ti ti-circle-check"></i> Done';
  var p=document.getElementById('p'+n);
  if(p){p.classList.remove('active');p.classList.add('done');}
  var next=document.getElementById('p'+(n+1));
  if(next){next.classList.add('active');}
}
</script>
</body>
